<HEADLINE>
FT  25 SEP 93 / Finance and the Family: Building society outflow worsens -
At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BUILDING societies suffered their worst outflow of funds this year, when
Pounds 132m was withdrawn in August following smaller net outflows in the
previous two months. There was a Pounds 61m outflow in July and a Pounds 56m
outflow in June. Adrian Coles, director-general of the Building Societies
Association, said the recent outflows of Pounds 249m needed to be balanced
against a Pounds 2.5bn inflow in the first half. He said that people were
withdrawing money to invest in equities, buy cars and fund the BT3 share
offer.
On the mortgage side, net new commitments of Pounds 2.43bn were the lowest
since January. Coles said: 'There are growing signs that house prices have
stabilised. This should help to underpin a recovery in activity over the
coming months, albeit from low levels.'
