FT  25 SEP 93 / International Company News: Lufthansa buys 25% of Sky Chefs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
LUFTHANSA, the German national airline, yesterday agreed to acquire a 25 per
cent stake in Sky Chefs, a Texas-based food service business, in a move
claimed to create the world's largest airline catering alliance with about
Dollars 1.3bn in revenues.
LSG Lufthansa Service, the airline's food-service division, is to buy one
quarter of Sky Chefs' existing stock for Dollars 75m. Onex, a diversified
Canadian group, currently owns 80 per cent of company, with Sky Chefs'
management holding the remainder.
Onex said the move was part of a global marketing accord between LSG
Lufthansa, the largest in-flight food operation in Europe and Asia, and Sky
Chefs, the second-biggest airline caterer in the US.
Sky Chefs has some Dollars 500m in turnover a year. The alliance will enable
the companies to provide food services to airlines on a worldwide basis.
