FT  25 SEP 93 / Gloomy figures for Japan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DAWKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Japanese consumers' gloomy mood was underlined yesterday by the lowest
August car production for 10 years and the 12th consecutive monthly decline
in chain store sales, writes William Dawkins from Tokyo.
Domestic vehicle production last month fell by 7.4 per cent from the same
month in 1992, as domestic and export demand both declined. Half the 10
companies surveyed by the Japan chain stores association reported that
business in September was recovering but they were not sure if sales had
bottomed out. Year on year, chain store sales fell by 2.1 per cent in
August.
